Posted July , July , Doug Spence Leave a comment Posted in Finances , Investing , Real Estate Guest article by Doug, founder of There are countless stories of individuals buying multiple homes they could not afford in the buildup to the housing market Many of these individuals had to file for bankruptcy as a result of their financial Every day, people buy homes they shouldn’t buy, and this is true for investment properties as Just because the bank will give you a loan for a property, doesn’t mean you are financially ready to buy that The banks are looking out for their bottom line – not So what are some things you should think about before you get that first investment property? Let’s dig Get Your Personal Finances in Order Ideally, you should have no consumer debt with the exception of a mortgage on a primary Consumer debt usually comes with rates and includes ‘bad debt’ like car payments, credit card debt, and Before you buy investment properties, you should aggressively pay down these loans and free yourself from Dave Ramsey has a great strategy for helping people become Paying these loans off ties into the next step: raise your credit score! Lenders need to see that you are a ‘good borrower’ which means you have steady income and you pay all your bills on You should target at least a credit You will also need cash reserves to cover surprise capital expenditures, vacancy costs, and I set aside $5,000 in a savings account per property . There are different ideas and techniques for addressing cash reserves, and I’ll admit mine is more conservative than most but it makes me sleep better at For example, if Stephen owns three properties, he would need to have $15,000 set aside for cash reserves, and get that number to $20,000 before he buys a Important disclaimer: These real estate cash reserves are different from your personal ‘emergency fund’ for unexpected personal expenses . Ok let’s sum up these up: No consumer Raise your credit score to at least Have sufficient real estate cash Make Sure Your Spouse Partner is % on Board People love surprises – but surprising your husband or wife with an investment property is a terrible It’s a big financial decision, so you should make sure you and your spouse are in Many times, an individual will have a much higher risk tolerance than their spouse – and this is totally You should sit down and have a serious conversation to determine your shared , goals, and strategies you are comfortable using to achieve those Maybe your spouse isn’t ok with you doing a with someone you met on the Bigger Pockets forum, but they would be ok with investing in an apartment syndication with someone you both know and The bottom line is: you have to communicate with your spouse partner and ensure you’re both on the same page before you commit to investing in anything – especially real Educate Yourself about Real Estate This one may seem obvious, and if you’re reading this article you’re already doing it! A cataract occurs when the eye’s natural lens becomes It’s the most common cause of vision loss in people over years old and is known as one of the main causes of blindness in the There are three different types of cataracts: Subcapsular cataracts, which occur at the back of the eye’s lens Nuclear cataracts, which form in the nucleus of the lens and are associated with aging Cortical cataracts, which begin to form in the periphery of the lens and work their way in At Carrot Eye Center, our years of experience allow us to create personalized care plans for every patient, no matter the type or severity of their Signs and Symptoms of Cataracts During the early development of a cataract, it won’t have much impact on your eyesight, but as it progresses, it will become noticeable: your vision may blur slightly, as if you are looking through clouded Cataracts can make light seem too bright, and things like headlights may cause more glare than they did Other symptoms include frequent changes in eye prescription and colors becoming faded or forming a yellow As you age, the proteins that comprise the lenses in your eyes begin to change their precise formation and clump This I typically pack 1 or 2 cork massage balls to take on my hiking and backpacking trips so I am prepared to roll out during and immediately During Your Hike That leads me nicely into during your When you are backpacking or hiking, have a dialog with Check in with your body with a scan starting at your toes and working your way Are there any warning lights on? You don t want to ignore these, because yellow warning lights easily become red emergency This applies especially to anything that could cause a critical failure (i.e. dizziness, trouble breathing, seeing spots). If you find yellow warning lights come on for muscular fatigue and tightness, you can pull out your tool and work out some of the tension right there on the After Your Hike Once your backpack is off and you re relaxing, it s time to do some serious Why? So you can get back out there, of course! The goal is to keep your muscles and tissue supple and flexible, so that you can prevent injury and build Again, I always pull out my cork massage ball after a hike and roll out key areas like feet (to prevent Plantar Fasciitis), IT Bands (to prevent knee pain), calves, hamstrings, quads, glutes, hips, back, chest, shoulders and Thru Hiking (Pacific Crest , Appalachian , Continental Divide , ) Ok, this is a whole new level of backpacking and, most certainly, requires a tremendous amount of to maintain the body for + Rawlogy balls are designed to be and compact, which means they re perfect for a thru hiker s Now, you just need to use them! We have assembled a collective of medical and biomechanics specialists, clinicians, engineers, product designers, and industry experts to create a more thoughtful way of improving gait and managing Ground Reaction Forces (GRF) using the latest in design and material innovations from a wide range of industries and Dynamic Motion Control Traditional ways of treating Lower Extremity (LE) pathologies involve using conventional bracing and supports utilize what we refer to as Static Motion Control . While somewhat effective, Static Motion Control can often lead to undesirable side effects, which include: muscle atrophy, soft tissue tightening, scar tissue , reduced Range of Motion (ROM), and the potential overloading of adjacent structures (which can cause other problems). We believe there s a better Dynamic Motion Control is the treatment of LE pathologies with precise, controlled SubioMed s Dynamic Motion Control technology promotes a proper gait in a fluid, controlled way, while also managing and minimizing the negative energies created by Ground Reaction Force (GRF). Dynamic Energy Return Sir Isaac Newton figured it out with the apple… Gravity + Human Motion = Ground Reaction Force (GRF) GRF is the exchange of energy between the earth and our body during ground Other than astronauts walking on the moon surface, GRF occurs during all three stages of contact (heel strike, midstance and ). The amount of GRF we encounter is determined by body weight, activity, type of ground, and angle of The effects of GRF can be gradual (aging) or rapid (injury). Regardless, GRF takes a toll on ways of minimizing GRF involve softer materials (inserts or shoe soles) and curved shoe We believe there s a better Dynamic Energy Return is SubioMed s patented, systematic approach to controlling Our unique designs reduce GRF at heel strike, store the energy through midstance, and deliver the energy for propulsion assist at Dynamic Energy Return technology promotes more comfortable, less injurious Hear about it Get updates on the latest products and innovations from SIGN UP Thank you for submitting! Privacy Policy – Frap Home Features Competition Support Login Sign Up 0 Privacy Policy This Privacy Policy describes how your personal information is collected, used, and shared when you visit or make a purchase from (the “Site”). Personal information we collect When you visit the Site, we automatically collect certain information about your device, including information about your web browser, IP address, time zone, and some of the cookies that are installed on your Additionally, as you browse the Site, we collect information about the individual web pages or products that you view, what websites or search terms referred you to the Site, and information about how you interact with the We refer to this information as “Device Information”. We collect Device Information using the following technologies: – “Cookies” are data files that are placed on your device or computer and often include an anonymous unique For more information about cookies, and how to disable cookies, visit http: www.allaboutcookies.org. – “Log files” track actions occurring on the Site, and collect data including your IP address, browser type, Internet service provider, referring exit pages, and date time – “Web beacons”, “tags”, and “pixels” are electronic files used to record information about how you browse the Additionally when you make a purchase or attempt to make a purchase through the Site, we collect certain information from you, including your name, billing address, shipping address, payment information (including credit card numbers), email address, and phone We refer to this information as “Order Information”. When we talk about “Personal Information” in this Privacy Policy, we are talking both about Device Information and Order How do we use your personal information? We use the Order Information that we collect generally to fulfill any orders placed through the Site (including processing your payment information, arranging for shipping, and providing you with invoices and or order confirmations). Additionally, we use this Order Information to: – Communicate with you – Screen our orders for potential risk or fraud and – When in line with the preferences you have shared with us, provide you with information or advertising relating to our products or We use the Device Information that we collect to help us screen for potential risk and fraud (in particular, your IP address), and more generally to improve and optimize our Site (for example, by generating analytics about how our customers browse and interact with the Site, and to assess the success of our marketing and advertising campaigns). Sharing you personal Information We share your Personal Information with third parties to help us use your Personal Information, as described For example, we use WooCommerce to power our online store–you can read more about how WooCommerce uses your Personal Information here: https: woocommerce.com privacy-policy . We also use Google Analytics to help us understand how our customers use the Site — you can read more about how Google uses your Personal Information here: https: www.google.com intl en policies privacy . You can also of Google Analytics here: https: tools.google.com dlpage gaoptout. Finally, we may also share your Personal Information to comply with applicable laws and regulations, to respond to a subpoena, search warrant or other lawful request for information we receive, or to otherwise protect our Behavioral advertising As described above, we use your Personal Information to provide you with targeted advertisements or marketing communications we believe may be of interest to For more information about how targeted advertising works, you can visit the Network Advertising Initiative’s (“NAI”) educational page at http: www.networkadvertising.org understanding-online-advertising how-does-it-work. San Luis Obispo | San Luis Obispo Guide skip to Main Content Cities San Luis Obispo Pismo Beach Paso Robles Cambria Morro Bay Avila Beach Arroyo Grande Atascadero Cayucos Creston Grover Beach Harmony Lake Nacimiento Los Osos Nipomo Oceano Ragged Point San Miguel San Simeon Santa Margarita Shandon Templeton Wineries Fun Events Calendar Submit an Event Weddings Food & Drink Lodging Shop Blog Menu San Luis Obispo Home » San Luis Obispo San Luis Obispo Creek, Downtown San Luis Obispo San Luis Obispo can be found in the heart of San Luis Obispo County along Highway in California, halfway between San Francisco and Los Angeles along the central As the largest city in in the county in both size and population, this college town experiences cool coastal weather with beaches to the north and south only minutes away, but also sees temperate winters due to the mountains, hills, and defunct volcanoes insulating the city from the harshest San Luis Obispo (or SLO as we locals call it) is also a short drive away from Paso Robles where visitors and locals can enjoy over wineries, and some of the sunniest weather in the This perfect location gives locals and visitors alike the chance to stay, play, eat, drink, and enjoy everything SLO and SLO County have to offer, and experience why people call this area the Happiest Place on Demographics San Luis Obispo County is still relatively small compared to other cities and counties in California, with ,177 people living in the entire county as of the Of the total population, % live in the city of San Luis Obispo (approx. ,451 individuals). This number can vary greatly, depending on when Cal Poly (the local university) is in From fall through spring college students can be found everywhere, but are replaced with the tourists in the summer once finals are done and students have gone Most Known For If you are lucky enough to find yourself in San Luis Obispo, there are five places you just can’t miss as you make your way through the city: Cal Poly San Luis Obispo San Luis Obispo is also home to California State Polytechnic University , or Cal Poly as we locals like to say, and you will know it the moment you walk through Cal Poly Pride runs deep in SLO, and it is worthwhile to see the campus or visit the gift shop and show off your Cal Poly Pride Go Mustangs! Madonna Inn The Madonna Inn is one of the most unique hotels in the entire county, and not because of an association with the The Madonna family are residents of SLO county, and their hotel has been a landmark on the central coast since it opened in Stop by for a piece of their pink champagne cake, or stay in one of their individually decorated rooms…and maybe sneak a peek at the waterfall urinal in the men’s restroom! San Luis Obispo Mission San Luis Obispo is home to one of the Spanish missions located in Built in by Father Junípero Serra, this hidden gem in downtown SLO is still open to the public for tours, mass, and special Locals and visitors alike can stroll through the gardens, visit the cemetery, or play by the fountains on hot summer days and celebrate the history and beauty the Mission brings to our Bishop Peak If you love hiking like most locals in SLO, then a visit to Bishop Peak is a must on your list of things to The 1,546 foot tall mountain rises high above San Luis Obispo, and offers stunning views of the city and surrounding areas from the Bishop Peak is also part of the chain of “Nine Sisters”, which are basically similar peaks that run from SLO to Morro Next time you find yourself in SLO make sure to make time for this hike, and then go celebrate with a piece of pink champagne cake at the Madonna Inn Bakery! Bubblegum Alley There is an alley in Downtown San Luis Obispo that is covered in Literally covered top to bottom in Locals and visitors alike take their chewed up gum and add it to this high by long alley for all the world to see, sometimes making it into shapes or their name as an added As gross as some people find it we locals take great pride in our Bubblegum Alley, so next time you are in SLO stop by and add your gum to the mix! Wineries San Luis Obispo County is already well known for their wines, especially the Paso Robles area where over wineries call What visitors (and many locals) don’t realize, though, is that San Luis Obispo and the surrounding region are also home to some incredible wineries that produce some amazing SLO technically falls within the Edna Valley wine region within San Luis Obispo County, and is home to individual The Edna Valley and Arroyo Grande wine regions are more for their Pinot Noirs and Chardonnays, crafted with grapes grown closer to the coast than those in Paso Robles grown in the heat and As you drive south from SLO on the it is easy to see the vineyards lining the highway, and if you are lucky enough you’ll even get to watch the harvesters in the There are also several companies within SLO county that host wine tours specifically in Edna You and a group of friends can

New Bern, Greenville & Wilmington Services Hearing Quiz Hearing Evaluation Testing Tinnitus Listening Device Consultations Products Phonak Oticon Lyric Widex Our Staff Georganne Carriere, , Rebecca Vlk Jason Rickman Sarah Brady Kelly McManus Courtney Palmiere Locations Greenville New Bern Wilmington Southpoint Charlotte Patient Info New Patient Forms Reasons for a Hearing Test Evaluation FAQ Blog Contact Select Page Tinnitus Tinnitus is a very common hearing condition for us to You’ve likely even seen advertisements for treatments for Tinnitus, also called Head Noises, presents itself in a variety of A constant sound “Ringing in the ears” A chirping sound, sometimes similar to a cricket A rustling sound A roar Various and shifting sounds Regardless of the exact sound, Tinnitus describes perceived noises that are only audible to the person experiencing This constant sound can be very irritating and usually causes the sufferer to seek Some may only find it mildly Either way, those experiencing these symptoms should see a hearing Sign of a greater problem? Simply because one has symptoms of Tinnitus does not mean there is a larger problem, but there could Tinnitus is often accompanied by hearing loss, especially to sounds, so it’s very important to have this addressed early to avoid further How do you pronounce “Tinnitus?” Tinnitus has two correct pronunciations: Tin’-uh-tus or ’-tis What causes Tinnitus? There are many different causes of Certain medications can cause the “ringing.” Other possible causes might include: High blood pressure Cardiovascular disease TMJ Musculoskeletal problems Tumors Noise exposure While the cause is not always evident, we do know it is not a sign of old Tinnitus affects people of all cultures and ages – including It is estimated that million Americans suffer from Treatment for Tinnitus There are treatments available for We have treated many people in New Bern, Greenville, and Wilmington for this condition and will be happy to evaluate and treat you, as Our Hours Mon – Thu 8:30AM – Friday 8:30AM – Extended hours available Contact Greenville New Bern Wilmington Southpoint Charlotte Quick Links Home Services Products Locations Notice of Privacy Practices Patient Forms Intake Form Receipt of NPP © Audiology | Site designed and managed by WRAL Digital Solutions WRAL Digital Solutions . | Privacy Policy   Phonak Hearing Aids | Audiology of NC - New Bern, Greenville & Wilmington Services Hearing Quiz Hearing Evaluation Testing Tinnitus Listening Device Consultations Products Phonak Oticon Lyr

Frequently Asked Questions | ToolBox Payment Primary Menu How It Works Features Industries About Pricing FAQ Welcome to ToolBox’s Frequently Asked Questions page This where you’ll find answers to commonly asked questions about payment If you don’t find what you’re looking for, please feel free to Contact Us ! What is a merchant account? Whether you are a service contractor, a pizza shop, a doctor, an website or the millions of other industry types , a merchant account is needed if you want to accept credit cards as a form of Home service contractors can accept various types of payments including cash, checks and credit cards (Visa, MasterCard, Discover and American Express). In order to accept these credit cards, a merchant account must first be set ToolBox offers 3 ways: (1) mobile payments app via your smartphone (2) virtual payment gateway using your computer point of sale system and (3) credit card Do You Have Hidden Fees? ToolBox’s pricing is very transparent and easy to understand… There’s no guesswork our pricing, that is sure! You see what you pay with each transaction—what you see is what you get, Plus you can always log in and see your rates and info at any time in your personal How About OddBall Fees? You never deal with odd fees that are added to throw you off… No startup fees, statement fees, weird refund fees, PCI scanning guideline fees, business card fees—etc. you understand… No How Much Extra Is It For Different Cards Like American Express? You pay the same rate for all the different credit cards… Visa, Mastercard, Discover, and, yes, even American Express all cost the same ToolBox doesn’t charge different rates for different credit How Do I Open A Merchant Account? Setting up a merchant account is easy with ToolBox… Download the ToolBox app from the app store and after completing our questionnaire, you will be approved very Many of our clients want a custom solution –whether it is working with an organization that wants a POS Solution for their corporate office and a mobile solution for their contractors on the In these cases, it is best to contact our office and will customize a solution that is right for your Is there a contract term if I open a merchant account? Many payment processing companies have contracts and termination This is a hidden fee in our At ToolBox, you can rest assured that we never charge a contract fee or a termination What is a merchant discount rate? A merchant discount rate is a percentage that is charged on every transaction accepted by a merchant for either the sale of a good or a service that has been It is the rate that has been assigned by the issuer of the card in conjunction with Visa, MasterCard, Discover, or American What is interchange? Interchange is the fee that Visa and MasterCard This is where there are a lot of hidden fees within the industry—there are more than interchange levels within Visa and There are rates for personal credit cards, reward credit cards, corporate credit cards, international credit cards, and debit credit All of these have a fee associated with So, for example, let’s say there is a swiped transaction, a transaction between a contractor and a Maybe the rate is 1 percent, but there is very low The contractor is swiping the card in However, if they get the card number over the phone then there’s more risk involved and the odds of fraud are For this reason, Visa and MasterCard put a higher rate and a higher So, maybe instead of 1% it increases to 3%. That interchange rate is universal across all credit card It’s the other fees that the processors put on top of that such as transaction fees and monthly fees and compliance fees that create the whole effective And what’s very important to understand is that many companies will take the lowest interchange So let’s say it’s % which sounds so They’ll say, “Hi , our rate is % and the truth is, they’re There is a rate that is %. If you get this particular credit card, you’ll be charged %, but it may be that out of a 1,000 transactions only one credit card hits that very low So, that’s why it’s so important that your credit card company shares with you an interchange summary and really breaks down for you every If you are considering switching processing partners or starting up, they should show you exactly what every fee should hit What is Toolbox’s flat fee for each payment? The transparent flat fee is % + per face to face For card not present transactions, the fee raises to % +.15. How long does it take to see the payment in my bank account? Transactions or a daily batch of transactions will get to your bank account the next business day as long as they are processed prior to eastern Monday to Any weekend batch gets processed on a Monday as the federal reserve that moves funds across bank lines are closed on the weekends and all federal Can I manually enter a customer’s credit card information? It’s a practice that combines conventional aquaculture—the raising of fish in tanks—with hydroponics—the cultivation of plants in water, creating a symbiotic environment for fish and plants to grow and It also allows us to grow food indoors all year long, use % less water than farms and encourage a % more rapid plant naturally! Our Promise, Delivered Superior Soil Sure, the quality of seeds is an important part of growing food, but the soil has a lot to do with it, We rely on biointensive, farming, cover crops, specialized composting, and crop rotation to get maximum yields from minimum We not only focus on what s happening above ground, but also what s occurring below the surface, for healthy soil biology that protects and helps our plants Sustainable Farming Conserve Water + more food Not only does this increase biodiversity, it sustains soil fertility by not disrupting critical Plus, this approach reduces soil erosion by nearly %, saves more than ,000 gallons of water per acre, produces two to six times more food, and builds fertile topsoil times faster than in Explore Our Meal Plans growing healthy, Join our newsletter for family discounts, healthy receipes, and Enter your email Instagram Facebook YouTube (688-7445) Reviews Contact Ambassador Program Corporate Health & Wellness Healthy Wholesaler Program © Nutrition For Longevity Meal Delivery PRIVACY • SHIPPING POLICY • REFUND POLICY Need a hand? Traditional root canal therapy can be stressful and We are here to change Why CORE Endodontics Your comfort is our From the first call you make to our practice through your root canal therapy, we want you to feel good that you chose CORE Amenities When you get here We provide things like: , cell phone chargers, magazines, a Nespresso coffee maker and other beverages to get you settled into our During your procedure Once you are seated for your procedure we invite you to stay cozy with a warm You can also zone out with our Bose noise cancelling After you re done Freshen up with a warm facial towel in our suite Grab a coffee or juice on your way out the Technology SonEndo GentleWave The GentleWave System is a significant advancment in root canal By using advanced fluid dynamics to create a vortex of procedure fluids that travel through your root canal system, helping to remove the tissue and debris that cause 1,2 Unlike standard root canal treatments, the GentleWave Ultracleaning Procedure is able to reach all throughout your tooth —even in the microscopic places 1,2 where bacteria can TrueVision We are excited to be the first office in Seattle to use this TrueVision is a magnification system that was originally developed for This system allows for magnification onto a inch TV TrueVision magnifies all the intricacies of a patient’s anatomy to identify every area of possible infection and The design of the system reduces fatigue for both the patient and Beam Computed Tomography The CBCT allows us to visually construct your tooth in which greatly increases the success of identifying all the anatomy of your tooth and the extent of the infection and Having this tomography allows us to decrease the time of the procedure while increasing the rate of We invested in a J Morita CBCT machine, considered the highest quality CBCT The J Morita gives the most precise image with the lowest amount of radiation (it produces less radiation than your average plane ride to Los Angeles). Single use files The FDA and manufacturers recommend using new rotary instruments for each patient, but it is common practice in the US to use files multiple times on multiple Our office chooses to use rotary instruments only one time and dispose of them after each patient in accordance with the manufacturer and FDA Electronic apex locator EAL measures the electrical current that lies within your body and tells us exactly where we should stop cleaning your This tool allows us to greatly reduce treatment time while increasing the success rate of the Press Seattle Met Our office is proud that Germack has been named to Seattle Met Top Dentist several The honor is an achievement that is decided upon by the dental community of Journal of Endodontics While completing his Endodontic residency at Oregon Health and Sciences University, Germack conducted research to gain a better use of antibiotics in root canal The research was published in October issue of the Journal of Endodontics .
